An ancient and revered topic. If you start to pursue the paranoid trains
of thought that haunt the subject you'll see that you probably shouldn't
even have the key entered via the laptop's chipset if you really want
the disk to be useless when removed. Which points to the need for a lump
in the ribbon cable with a HW key + lengthy PIN.

Mike

